<h2>Drunken Thunder God</h2>

<p><strong>Class:</strong> Warlock (Hexblade) / Monk (Drunken Master) / Fighter (Battle Master)</p>
<p><strong>Race:</strong> Any (recommended: Half-Orc for <em>Savage Attacks</em>)</p>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Custom</p>

<h3>Stats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Strength:</strong> 8 (boosted via flasks)</li>
    <li><strong>Dexterity:</strong> 16 (15 + 1)</li>
    <li><strong>Constitution:</strong> 14</li>
    <li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> 8</li>
    <li><strong>Wisdom:</strong> 10</li>
    <li><strong>Charisma:</strong> 17 (15 + 2, boosted to 22 via Hag Hair + ASIs)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Build Summary</h3>
<p>
    This build is a chaotic fusion of thunder, rage, and drunken mastery. You’ll start as a Hexblade Warlock for weapon binding and spell utility, then dive into Monk for mobility and flair, and finish with Fighter for raw damage and tactical superiority. The synergy between <strong>Booming Blade</strong>, <strong>Sweeping Attack</strong>, and <strong>Great Weapon Master</strong> turns you into a thunderous whirlwind of destruction.
</p>

<h3>Character Progression</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Level 1:</strong> Warlock (Hexblade) — Bind Hexed Weapon, Booming Blade, Eldritch Blast, Shield, Armor of Agathys</li>
    <li><strong>Levels 2–4:</strong> Monk — gain Monk passives, choose <strong>Way of the Drunken Master</strong> at Monk 3</li>
    <li><strong>Level 5:</strong> Monk 4 — choose <strong>Great Weapon Master</strong> feat</li>
    <li><strong>Level 6:</strong> Fighter 1 — choose Fighting Style: Great Weapon Fighting or Defense</li>
    <li><strong>Level 7:</strong> Fighter 2 — gain <strong>Action Surge</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Level 8:</strong> Fighter 3 — subclass into <strong>Battle Master</strong>, choose 3 Manoeuvres (must include <strong>Sweeping Attack</strong>)</li>
    <li><strong>Level 9:</strong> Fighter 4 — ASI: +2 Charisma (to 20)</li>
    <li><strong>Level 10:</strong> Fighter 5 — gain <strong>Extra Attack</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Level 11:</strong> Fighter 6 — ASI: +2 Charisma (to 22)</li>
    <li><strong>Level 12:</strong> Fighter 7 — gain short rest recovery of superiority dice, more Manoeuvres (e.g. Pushing Attack, Disarm)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Feats</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Great Weapon Master:</strong> +10 damage on two-handed attacks, toggleable -5 to hit</li>
    <li><strong>Ability Score Improvements:</strong> Charisma +2 (twice), optional Dexterity +2</li>
</ul>

<h3>Key Spells & Cantrips</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Booming Blade:</strong> Core damage engine</li>
    <li><strong>Eldritch Blast:</strong> Optional ranged utility</li>
    <li><strong>Shield:</strong> +5 AC reaction</li>
    <li><strong>Armor of Agathys:</strong> Bonus survivability</li>
</ul>

<h3>Equipment (Endgame)</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Helmet:</strong> Helldusk Helmet — Devil’s Sight, +2 spell saves, immune to crits</li>
    <li><strong>Cloak:</strong> Cloak of Protection — +1 AC</li>
    <li><strong>Armor:</strong> Armor of Dexterity — AC scales with Dexterity</li>
    <li><strong>Gloves:</strong> Gloves of Belligerent Skies — thunder damage conversion</li>
    <li><strong>Boots:</strong> Boots of Stormy Clamor — thunder damage conversion</li>
    <li><strong>Amulet:</strong> Amulet of Greater Health — sets Constitution to 23</li>
    <li><strong>Ring 1:</strong> Callous Glow Ring — +2 damage to lit targets</li>
    <li><strong>Ring 2:</strong> Ring of Protection — +1 AC</li>
    <li><strong>Weapon:</strong> Punch-Drunk Bastard — core weapon of the build</li>
</ul>

<h3>Playstyle Tips</h3>
<p>
    Open fights with Booming Blade and Sweeping Attack to spread thunder damage across multiple enemies. Use Action Surge to chain devastating combos. Your AC is high, your Charisma is monstrous, and your thunder damage is everywhere. Throw in a drunken stagger and laugh as enemies fall.
</p>